# .aiexclude — exclude everything except an explicit small allowlist
# Intent: keep AI models and code assistants from indexing or suggesting changes
# to most of the repository. Only the source tree and a few root files are
# intentionally allowed for AI assistance.

# -- Default: ignore everything --
../src

# -- Allow this config file so the assistant can read/update it --
!.aiexclude

# -- Allow the main source tree --
!src/
!src/**

# -- Allow primary build/config files to be visible to AI assistants --
!build.gradle.kts
!AGENTS.md
!local.env

# Notes:
# - This file uses gitignore-style patterns (negation via `!`). Some AI tooling
#   that reads .aiexclude follows this convention. If your tooling expects a
#   different format, tell me and I can adapt the file.
# - Currently this intentionally hides other repo files (e.g. `settings.gradle.kts`,
#   `gradlew`, `gradle/`, `container/`, `README.md`). If you want any of those
#   visible to the assistant (recommended for building/running the project),
#   I can add them to the allowlist.
# - Example additions you may want to allow: `settings.gradle.kts`, `gradlew`,
#   `gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.properties`, `container/docker-compose.yml`,
#   `README.md`.

